line_2: Th'exhausted mourner mopes, then wildly stalks

line_1: He seems a dauncing as he walks,
But sails secure on gravel walks.
line_2: No more in ponds the gosling talks,

line_1: There shall the grove divide its tepid walks.
line_2: Spreads o'er the heath its slender prickly stalks;

line_1: But, for my part, whene'er she walks,
line_2: Each fool of Delia's figure talks,

line_1: Dauntless as Death away He walks;
line_2: Breaks the Doors open; snaps the Locks;

line_1: Slow, o'er the twilight sands or leafy walks,
Plays round her steps, and guards her favour'd walks;
line_2: — And now a spotted Pard the lover stalks,

line_1: And humbler bean midst her own fragrance walks.
line_2: There the tall pea in stately grandeur stalks,

line_1: And all a goddess as she walks,
line_2: Tho' all a syren as she talks,

line_1: A Pipkin there like Homer's Tripod walks;
line_2: Here sighs a Jar, and there a Goose-pye talks;

line_1: Looks back and trembles as he walks,
line_2: Along the silent room he stalks,
